## Step 1 - add-camera-proxy-routes
Done
Added new Node-RED HTTP routes for `/api/camera/stream` and `/api/camera/capture` in `flow.json`.
Both routes now go through server-side request chains with explicit response nodes.

## Step 2 - switch-camera-config-to-relative
Done
Updated `cameraConfig` in `flow.json` to publish relative URLs for stream and capture endpoints.
The camera host is now resolved from flow/global/env with a safe default and sanitized value.

## Step 3 - harden-client-defaults
Done
Replaced direct LAN-IP defaults in `camera-panel.js` with server-local fallback endpoints.
This removes direct browser fallback attempts to `192.168.x.x` when config values are missing.

## Step 4 - verify-cross-subnet-path
Done
Validated `flow.json` syntax by parsing it with Node.js and checking endpoint references via search.
Confirmed config now points stream/capture to `/api/camera/*` instead of direct camera LAN URLs.

## Step 5 - update-implementation-log
Done
Created this `implementation-plan.mdc` file because it did not exist in project root.
Documented each plan step in order with required Done marker and two-line work summary.

## Step 6 - multi-camera-registry-and-proxy-refactor
Done
Refactored `flow.json` camera endpoints from fixed single host to camera registry resolution by `cameraId` with persistent store fallback.
Added multi-camera management APIs (`/api/cameras`, `/api/cameras/:id`, `/api/cameras/active`) and removed all fixed `10...178` dependencies.

## Step 7 - camera-panel-1-1-multi-camera-ui
Done
Rebuilt `camera-panel.js` to support adding cameras, selecting active camera, managing list, and switching between single-view and tile-view.
Updated runtime `cameraPanelJs` script in `flow.json` so `/api/camera-panel.js` serves multi-camera UI behavior without fixed host assumptions.

## Step 8 - validation-and-hardening
Done
Verified no remaining fixed-IP camera references and no `cameraHost` fallback dependencies tied to the old single-camera model.
Prepared flow and client logic for restart-safe behavior by persisting camera registry in file-backed context when available.

## Step 9 - proxy-first-stream-strategy
Done
Refactored stream connection logic to prioritize proxy URLs over direct camera access for universal Tailscale compatibility.
Reduced timeout from 9s to 3s, adjusted reconnect attempts (proxy: 3, direct: 2), and updated both single-view and tile-view to use proxy-first approach.
